paragraphs.content:
This Agreement is made by and between the parties identified below:
   @employment_employer_company_name incorporated and registered in @employment_employer_jurisdiction with company number @employment_employer_registration_number whose registered office is at @employment_employer_address (the "Employer") 

   @employment_employee_individual_name: @employment_employee_address - @employment_employee_email (the "Employee") 

(The Employer and the Employee may hereinafter be collectively referred to as "Parties" and each individually as "Party").

The Employee’s commission shall be calculated on a tiered basis according to the following schedule:
   For sales up to @employment_sale_com_tier1_threshold, a commission rate of @employment_sale_com_tier1_rate shall apply;
   For sales exceeding @employment_sale_com_tier1_threshold and up to @employment_sale_com_tier2_threshold, a commission rate of @employment_sale_com_tier2_rate shall apply on the amount within this range;
   For sales exceeding @employment_sale_com_tier2_threshold, a commission rate of @employment_sale_com_tier3_rate shall apply on the amount exceeding this threshold.
Commissions shall be payable within @employment_sales_commission_payment_duration following the end of the @employment_sales_commission_calculation_time_unit in which the revenue is recognized.

The Employee shall:
   Keep all Confidential Information strictly confidential and not disclose or permit the disclosure of such information to any person other than an officer, authorized employee, or representative of the Employer who has a need to know such information in the course of their duties and who is subject to confidentiality obligations;
   Use Confidential Information only as strictly required in the performance of the Employee’s duties;
take all reasonable precautions to protect the confidentiality of such information, including compliance with all applicable policies, procedures, and any additional measures the Employer may reasonably require from time to time;
Return to the Employer all Confidential Information in the Employee’s possession immediately upon request by the Employer and, in any event, upon the termination or expiration of employment.

The Employee is required to promptly declare in writing to their Appropriate Manager any actual, potential, or perceived conflict of interest that arises during the term of employment. This includes, but is not limited to:
Financial interests in, or personal relationships with, any customer, supplier, contractor, or competitor of the Employer;
Acceptance of gifts, hospitality, or benefits from any business partner, client, supplier, or competitor;
   Any outside employment, consultancy, business, or directorship, whether paid or unpaid, that may be in competition with, or otherwise impact, the Employee’s ability to perform their duties for the Employer;
Any personal, professional, or financial interest that might influence, or reasonably be perceived to influence, the Employee’s judgment or actions in the course of their duties.

This clause shall not prohibit the Employee from:
Making truthful statements as required by law or in response to a valid subpoena or legal process;
Communicating with any government or regulatory authority as part of lawful whistleblowing or reporting obligations;
Exercising any rights protected under applicable employment laws, including reporting unlawful or unethical conduct.
